HW3: scene  

Connor Davel
CSCI4229 2022


Demonstrates how to draw a scene


Key bindings
  arrows     Change view angle
  0          Reset view angle
  9          Reset position
  o/l        increase/decrease z position
  r/f/d/g    change x and y view position
  ESC        Exit
Tree types:
  There are 2 type of trees with various parameters that 
  are copied, rotated, and generally changed throughout 
  the scene. The rotation and size of the branches/leaves
  is varied randomly as well as the size. 

Sources:
No outside sources used. All code is from in-class examples,
especially example 8 for things like window resizing, drawing lines/axes,
drawing a sphere, etc. 

Time to Complete:
about 6 hours